Parliament, Tuesday, 11 September 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs will tomorrow start with the second phase of the investigation into the process followed in the naturalisation of the Gupta family. Tomorrow the committee will listen to evidence by the following individuals and organisations: Details of the Meeting 
	Date: 12 September 2018
	Venue: Old Assembly Chamber
	Time: 08:30 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON HOME AFFAIRS, MR HLOMANI CHAUKE. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
